<theorem xml:id="lecture-notes-rational-root-theorem">
  <title>Rational Root Theorem</title>
  <p>Let <m>p(x)</m> be any polynomial function with leading coefficient <m>a_n</m> and constant term <m>a_0</m>. Then any rational root has the form <m>\frac{p}{q}</m>, where <m>p</m> divides <m>a_0</m> and <m>q</m> divides <m>a_n</m>.</p>
</theorem>

